00:00:09.376 --> 00:00:11.011 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KURAHASHI]
You disappoint me, Little Devil.

00:00:11.144 --> 00:00:13.013 position:44% line:83% align:start
Even
with all the illegal abilities

00:00:13.146 --> 00:00:14.414 position:35% line:89% align:start
I gave you,

00:00:14.549 --> 00:00:17.184 position:27% line:83% align:start
you still failed
to defeat one measly little rat.

00:00:17.585 --> 00:00:19.687 position:16% line:83% align:start
You really are worthless,
aren't you?

00:00:19.821 --> 00:00:21.321 position:13% line:89% align:start
Just an untalented nobody.

00:00:21.455 --> 00:00:24.291 position:30% line:83% align:start
To be held back
by some girl like you...

00:00:24.424 --> 00:00:26.460 position:19% line:83% align:start
I hope you didn't think
those favors were free.

00:00:26.594 --> 00:00:28.630 position:13% line:83% align:start
You're going to pay me back
and then some.

00:00:29.096 --> 00:00:30.230 position:35% line:89% align:start
Aren't you?

00:00:31.031 --> 00:00:32.867 position:7% line:89% align:start
From today on, you're my slave,

00:00:33.001 --> 00:00:36.036 position:30% line:83% align:start
a useless thing
to carry out my every whim.

00:00:36.804 --> 00:00:37.705 position:41% line:89% align:start
[slams]

00:00:38.071 --> 00:00:40.742 position:10% line:89% align:start
Do you understand me? Say it!

00:00:41.141 --> 00:00:43.811 position:7% line:89% align:start
From today on, I'm your slave.

00:00:43.945 --> 00:00:45.013 position:41% line:89% align:start
[slams]

00:00:45.145 --> 00:00:46.146 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:00:46.280 --> 00:00:49.149 position:13% line:89% align:start
Yeah as if, like I'd ever.

00:00:49.684 --> 00:00:51.019 position:35% line:89% align:start
Ooh, scary.

00:00:51.184 --> 00:00:52.954 position:16% line:89% align:start
Here comes a real devil.

00:00:53.086 --> 00:00:54.354 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KURAHASHI]
Hiroto Shinohara?

00:00:54.889 --> 00:00:57.157 position:21% line:83% align:start
[gasps] What the hell
are you doing here?

00:00:57.291 --> 00:01:00.562 position:35% line:89% align:start
[footsteps]

00:01:00.695 --> 00:01:02.062 position:27% line:89% align:start
No, not just me.

00:01:02.195 --> 00:01:05.432 position:35% line:89% align:start
[hovering]

00:01:05.567 --> 00:01:06.466 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:01:08.736 --> 00:01:09.604 position:44% line:89% align:start
Ah...

00:01:09.737 --> 00:01:12.574 position:27% line:83% align:start
[scoffs] Come on,
smile, Kurahashi.

00:01:12.974 --> 00:01:14.374 position:16% line:89% align:start
Show those pearly whites

00:01:14.509 --> 00:01:16.844 position:10% line:83% align:start
to the hundreds of thousands
of people watching.

00:01:18.580 --> 00:01:19.479 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:01:22.784 --> 00:01:26.788 position:38% line:89% align:start
[fuming]

00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:32.860 position:10% line:89% align:start
Sorry, pal, that's checkmate.

00:01:38.131 --> 00:01:39.399 position:24% line:89% align:start
[ICHINOSE exhales]

00:01:39.534 --> 00:01:40.969 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ICHINOSE]
Well, good morning, everyone.

00:01:41.101 --> 00:01:43.738 position:10% line:83% align:start
You know, something wonderful
happened yesterday.

00:01:44.204 --> 00:01:45.873 position:38% line:83% align:start
[giggles]
An incompetent dictator

00:01:46.007 --> 00:01:49.010 position:24% line:83% align:start
was finally exposed
as the scumbag he is.

00:01:49.142 --> 00:01:50.545 position:41% line:83% align:start
Despite
his distinguished bearing,

00:01:50.678 --> 00:01:52.212 position:7% line:89% align:start
he was a manipulative con man,

00:01:52.346 --> 00:01:55.248 position:19% line:83% align:start
whose empire collapsed
in a single evening.

00:01:55.382 --> 00:01:56.718 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm actually still
a little groggy

00:01:56.851 --> 00:01:59.087 position:33% line:83% align:start
from a night
of celebratory drinking.

00:01:59.219 --> 00:02:00.387 position:30% line:89% align:start
So bear with me

00:02:00.521 --> 00:02:02.090 position:24% line:83% align:start
if today's address
is a bit shaky.

00:02:02.590 --> 00:02:04.926 position:19% line:83% align:start
Now, as the All-Campus
Elimination Battle

00:02:05.059 --> 00:02:06.561 position:16% line:89% align:start
has reached its terminus,

00:02:06.694 --> 00:02:09.162 position:13% line:83% align:start
allow me to present to you
our two remaining survivors.

00:02:09.296 --> 00:02:12.734 position:16% line:83% align:start
First up, the Seven Star,
Hiroto Shinohara.

00:02:13.133 --> 00:02:14.334 position:5% line:89% align:start
Although, that's kind of a given

00:02:14.468 --> 00:02:15.670 position:13% line:89% align:start
seeing as how anything less

00:02:15.803 --> 00:02:17.538 position:30% line:83% align:start
would make him
a total laughingstock.

00:02:18.305 --> 00:02:20.407 position:10% line:83% align:start
Weirdly threatening addendum,
but okay.

00:02:20.808 --> 00:02:22.844 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ICHINOSE]
Next is the Little Devil,

00:02:22.977 --> 00:02:25.013 position:13% line:89% align:start
the Six Star, Noa Akizuki.

00:02:25.145 --> 00:02:26.114 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:02:26.246 --> 00:02:27.347 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:02:27.782 --> 00:02:28.616 position:24% line:89% align:start
Both are confirmed

00:02:28.750 --> 00:02:30.317 position:27% line:83% align:start
for the district
elimination team,

00:02:30.450 --> 00:02:33.186 position:21% line:83% align:start
but only one of them
can be titled Eimei's Ace.

00:02:33.320 --> 00:02:34.488 position:21% line:89% align:start
A final confrontation

00:02:34.622 --> 00:02:36.189 position:21% line:83% align:start
between the Six Star
and the Seven.

00:02:36.323 --> 00:02:37.157 position:16% line:89% align:start
Get ready for an amazi--

00:02:37.290 --> 00:02:38.458 position:27% line:89% align:start
Um, Headmistress?

00:02:38.593 --> 00:02:40.662 position:13% line:89% align:start
May I please say something?

00:02:41.062 --> 00:02:42.664 position:38% line:89% align:start
I, uh...

00:02:43.064 --> 00:02:44.197 position:24% line:89% align:start
I don't want to...

00:02:44.565 --> 00:02:46.567 position:10% line:83% align:start
[sighs] I don't want to fight
against Hiroto.

00:02:46.701 --> 00:02:48.803 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Mm...
-And would you care to tell us

00:02:48.936 --> 00:02:50.404 position:27% line:89% align:start
why exactly not?

00:02:50.538 --> 00:02:52.740 position:24% line:83% align:start
I think most people
have already heard this by now,

00:02:52.874 --> 00:02:55.308 position:27% line:83% align:start
but in my desire
to escape feeling less than,

00:02:55.442 --> 00:02:57.779 position:41% line:83% align:start
I made
some reprehensible choices.

00:02:57.912 --> 00:02:59.346 position:19% line:89% align:start
I used illegal methods,

00:02:59.479 --> 00:03:01.749 position:13% line:83% align:start
and I tried to steal Stars
from Hiroto.

00:03:01.883 --> 00:03:03.450 position:21% line:89% align:start
For that, I'm sorry.

00:03:03.584 --> 00:03:05.853 position:19% line:83% align:start
Ultimately, my attempts
came to nothing anyway,

00:03:05.987 --> 00:03:08.723 position:19% line:83% align:start
but while everyone else
was competing in good faith,

00:03:08.856 --> 00:03:11.425 position:35% line:83% align:start
my conduct
was wholly unacceptable.

00:03:11.559 --> 00:03:13.995 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, it only makes sense
that I withdraw--

00:03:14.128 --> 00:03:15.429 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
That's enough, Akizuki.

00:03:15.563 --> 00:03:17.598 position:7% line:89% align:start
Uh? Is something wrong, Hiroto?

00:03:17.732 --> 00:03:19.199 position:7% line:89% align:start
You've got absolutely no reason

00:03:19.332 --> 00:03:20.902 position:33% line:83% align:start
-to withdraw.
-Huh?

00:03:21.035 --> 00:03:23.604 position:16% line:83% align:start
It was all that sleazebag
Kurahashi's fault.

00:03:23.738 --> 00:03:25.673 position:19% line:83% align:start
I didn't lose anything
in the end.

00:03:25.807 --> 00:03:28.009 position:35% line:83% align:start
Well, yeah,
but nobody's going to forgive me

00:03:28.142 --> 00:03:29.177 position:24% line:89% align:start
for what I've done!

00:03:29.309 --> 00:03:30.778 position:21% line:83% align:start
-[HIROTO] You think?
-Ah...

00:03:30.912 --> 00:03:32.412 position:10% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Then you might want
to take a look at this.

00:03:34.115 --> 00:03:35.149 position:44% line:83% align:start
[NOA]
What is that?

00:03:35.817 --> 00:03:37.785 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
It's a survey of Eimei students.

00:03:37.919 --> 00:03:40.387 position:21% line:83% align:start
Libra carried it out
right after the stream ended.

00:03:40.521 --> 00:03:42.190 position:7% line:89% align:start
Just take a look for yourself.

00:03:42.724 --> 00:03:45.258 position:33% line:83% align:start
A good 99.5%
of the students here

00:03:45.392 --> 00:03:46.728 position:16% line:89% align:start
actually took your side,

00:03:46.861 --> 00:03:48.830 position:16% line:83% align:start
which means the consensus
of Eimei Academy

00:03:48.963 --> 00:03:51.398 position:10% line:83% align:start
-is that you're not at fault.
-[NOA gasps]

00:03:51.532 --> 00:03:52.934 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Honestly,

00:03:53.067 --> 00:03:54.569 position:21% line:83% align:start
and you think people
don't pay attention to you?

00:03:54.702 --> 00:03:57.270 position:16% line:83% align:start
I mean, even our Empress
was singing your praises.

00:03:57.404 --> 00:03:58.973 position:35% line:89% align:start
They what?

00:03:59.874 --> 00:04:01.008 position:30% line:89% align:start
Look, Akizuki.

00:04:01.142 --> 00:04:03.144 position:7% line:83% align:start
You got carried away for a bit,
that's all.

00:04:03.945 --> 00:04:06.881 position:33% line:83% align:start
The truth is,
you'd already become special,

00:04:07.014 --> 00:04:07.982 position:27% line:89% align:start
all by yourself.

00:04:09.016 --> 00:04:10.350 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[sniffles]
-[HIROTO] With that said,

00:04:10.484 --> 00:04:11.953 position:7% line:89% align:start
I have an announcement to make.

00:04:12.787 --> 00:04:14.856 position:35% line:83% align:start
The winner
of the Elimination contest,

00:04:14.989 --> 00:04:17.859 position:24% line:83% align:start
and Eimei Academy's
rightful ace, is you.

00:04:18.391 --> 00:04:19.894 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:04:20.027 --> 00:04:22.163 position:19% line:83% align:start
Sorry, but the only one
who's withdrawing here is me.

00:04:22.295 --> 00:04:23.765 position:13% line:89% align:start
But don't you want to win?

00:04:23.898 --> 00:04:25.533 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Why would I need to?

00:04:25.666 --> 00:04:27.769 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm already the strongest person
on the island, right?

00:04:27.902 --> 00:04:29.771 position:24% line:89% align:start
Uh... Yeah, but...

00:04:29.904 --> 00:04:31.139 position:27% line:89% align:start
Sorry, it's done.

00:04:31.271 --> 00:04:32.439 position:27% line:89% align:start
I just submitted

00:04:32.573 --> 00:04:33.975 position:7% line:83% align:start
the official player-withdrawal
request.

00:04:34.108 --> 00:04:36.376 position:13% line:83% align:start
So, for all those out there
who bet money on me,

00:04:36.511 --> 00:04:37.779 position:27% line:89% align:start
sucks to be you.

00:04:38.311 --> 00:04:39.446 position:27% line:83% align:start
[MALE STUDENT 7A]
Can he do that?

00:04:40.081 --> 00:04:41.916 position:24% line:83% align:start
[FEMALE STUDENT 7C]
The Seven Star quit?

00:04:42.049 --> 00:04:44.384 position:7% line:83% align:start
There. Now you've got something
to prove that you're special.

00:04:44.519 --> 00:04:46.053 position:35% line:89% align:start
[whimpers]

00:04:46.486 --> 00:04:48.589 position:35% line:83% align:start
All right,
if that's what you want,

00:04:48.723 --> 00:04:50.792 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'll accept the position of ace.

00:04:50.925 --> 00:04:53.326 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll become the ace
this academy deserves,

00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:55.428 position:13% line:83% align:start
one that can face even you,
Hiroto.

00:04:55.897 --> 00:04:59.466 position:5% line:83% align:start
So please, lend me your support,
and I'll make all of you proud!

00:04:59.600 --> 00:05:01.736 position:24% line:89% align:start
[STUDENTS cheering]

00:05:01.869 --> 00:05:03.638 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ICHINOSE]
That Shinohara.

00:05:03.771 --> 00:05:05.006 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggles]

00:05:05.139 --> 00:05:07.708 position:5% line:83% align:start
This year's Inter-Academy Battle
might actually be fun

00:05:07.842 --> 00:05:08.810 position:27% line:89% align:start
with him around.

00:05:09.243 --> 00:05:10.111 position:30% line:89% align:start
Here they are!

00:05:10.244 --> 00:05:11.546 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:05:11.679 --> 00:05:15.116 position:10% line:83% align:start
The flawless high-spec maid,
Shirayuki Himeji!

00:05:15.249 --> 00:05:16.416 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Way to go, Himeji!

00:05:16.551 --> 00:05:18.519 position:21% line:83% align:start
Back up to Four Stars
in one day!

00:05:19.053 --> 00:05:21.189 position:30% line:83% align:start
[ICHINOSE] One
of Eimei's trio of Six Stars,

00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:24.324 position:27% line:83% align:start
the Golden Demon,
Nanase Asamiya!

00:05:24.457 --> 00:05:26.426 position:24% line:83% align:start
Next, the Six Star
student council president

00:05:26.561 --> 00:05:27.829 position:24% line:89% align:start
with second sight,

00:05:27.962 --> 00:05:29.329 position:30% line:89% align:start
Shinji Enomoto!

00:05:29.462 --> 00:05:30.932 position:33% line:83% align:start
You know him
as the highest-ranked

00:05:31.065 --> 00:05:32.332 position:24% line:89% align:start
on Academy Island,

00:05:32.465 --> 00:05:34.635 position:10% line:89% align:start
Seven Star, Hiroto Shinohara!

00:05:34.769 --> 00:05:38.239 position:10% line:83% align:start
And finally, Eimei's new ace,
the Little Devil,

00:05:38.371 --> 00:05:40.007 position:19% line:89% align:start
Six Star, Noa Akizuki!

00:05:40.575 --> 00:05:42.310 position:24% line:83% align:start
These are the five
who will represent us

00:05:42.442 --> 00:05:45.012 position:5% line:89% align:start
in the May Inter-Academy Battle!

00:05:45.445 --> 00:05:46.614 position:27% line:83% align:start
[MALE STUDENT 7D]
You got this!

00:05:46.747 --> 00:05:48.182 position:27% line:83% align:start
[MALE STUDENT 7E]
Put on a good show!

00:05:48.316 --> 00:05:51.152 position:13% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Not a bad outcome,
all things considered.

00:05:51.285 --> 00:05:52.320 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
You can say that again.

00:05:52.452 --> 00:05:53.554 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm just glad the Little Devil

00:05:53.688 --> 00:05:54.989 position:27% line:83% align:start
didn't get kicked
off the island.

00:05:55.656 --> 00:05:57.291 position:30% line:83% align:start
Still, though,
as an Ouka student,

00:05:57.424 --> 00:05:58.926 position:7% line:89% align:start
I can't be too happy about it.

00:05:59.060 --> 00:06:00.161 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:06:00.294 --> 00:06:02.063 position:35% line:83% align:start
Yeah, well,
it's not like she was let off

00:06:02.196 --> 00:06:03.598 position:19% line:89% align:start
without any penalties.

00:06:03.731 --> 00:06:05.365 position:30% line:83% align:start
As compensation
for all the trouble she caused,

00:06:05.498 --> 00:06:06.834 position:7% line:89% align:start
she forked over the Green Star.

00:06:06.968 --> 00:06:08.401 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
You got the green, too?

00:06:08.536 --> 00:06:10.304 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, that makes you what
in reality?

00:06:10.437 --> 00:06:11.973 position:10% line:89% align:start
A triple-colored three star?

00:06:12.106 --> 00:06:13.373 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Yup, bingo.

00:06:13.841 --> 00:06:16.409 position:10% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] I'm still a ways off
from being a real Seven Star,

00:06:16.544 --> 00:06:18.411 position:19% line:83% align:start
but if I keep on moving
towards that goal,

00:06:18.546 --> 00:06:19.847 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'll find her.

00:06:19.981 --> 00:06:22.183 position:16% line:83% align:start
So, when do I get to know
where you're dragging me

00:06:22.316 --> 00:06:23.751 position:19% line:89% align:start
on my precious day off?

00:06:23.885 --> 00:06:24.785 position:35% line:89% align:start
Right now.

00:06:26.120 --> 00:06:26.954 position:35% line:89% align:start
We're here.

00:06:27.088 --> 00:06:28.455 position:38% line:89% align:start
Mm! Ah...

00:06:28.923 --> 00:06:30.390 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
What's this all about, Saionji?

00:06:30.524 --> 00:06:31.826 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
Huh? What do you mean?

00:06:31.959 --> 00:06:33.561 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's exactly what it looks like.

00:06:33.694 --> 00:06:36.429 position:16% line:83% align:start
Listen, this store sells
some awesome stuff,

00:06:36.564 --> 00:06:38.633 position:16% line:83% align:start
like the card I gave you
the other night.

00:06:39.432 --> 00:06:40.768 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
No kidding.

00:06:40.902 --> 00:06:42.469 position:16% line:83% align:start
So this is where you got
that Pinch Hitter, huh?

00:06:42.603 --> 00:06:44.338 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] This is the place,
all right, but to get you in,

00:06:44.471 --> 00:06:47.341 position:24% line:83% align:start
you have to satisfy
their weird entry requirement.

00:06:47.708 --> 00:06:49.476 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Yeah, but this?

00:06:50.044 --> 00:06:51.913 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
Look, I mentioned it, didn't I?

00:06:52.046 --> 00:06:53.981 position:19% line:83% align:start
That I needed your help
getting in somewhere?

00:06:54.115 --> 00:06:56.317 position:33% line:83% align:start
If anything,
you should consider it an honor.

00:06:56.449 --> 00:06:57.952 position:7% line:89% align:start
Even if it's just for a while,

00:06:58.085 --> 00:07:01.122 position:19% line:83% align:start
you get to be my lover,
or whatever you would call it.

00:07:02.723 --> 00:07:04.025 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Whoa.

00:07:04.825 --> 00:07:06.060 position:16% line:89% align:start
I did give her a heads-up

00:07:06.193 --> 00:07:08.095 position:21% line:83% align:start
that I'd swinging by
with some company.

00:07:09.163 --> 00:07:10.631 position:24% line:89% align:start
Anyone back there?

00:07:11.065 --> 00:07:12.033 position:33% line:89% align:start
Hey! Welcome!

00:07:12.166 --> 00:07:14.902 position:35% line:83% align:start
Wait, Lily?
What are you doing here?

00:07:15.403 --> 00:07:17.271 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
"Lily"? Oh, yeah.

00:07:17.405 --> 00:07:19.240 position:7% line:89% align:start
She can't use her other names.

