00:13:52.600 --> 00:13:54.001 position:10% line:83% align:start
I've got a loud-mouthed idiot
standing next to me,

00:13:54.134 --> 00:13:55.570 position:16% line:89% align:start
so I'm practically deaf.

00:13:55.704 --> 00:13:56.970 position:38% line:83% align:start
[NANASE]
I wouldn't have to shout

00:13:57.104 --> 00:13:58.205 position:13% line:89% align:start
if you'd stop being a jerk!

00:13:58.339 --> 00:13:59.708 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-They swear up and down

00:13:59.840 --> 00:14:01.241 position:13% line:89% align:start
that they hate each other,

00:14:01.375 --> 00:14:03.911 position:16% line:83% align:start
but they're never apart,
so every time you see them.

00:14:04.044 --> 00:14:05.312 position:30% line:89% align:start
[door sliding]

00:14:05.446 --> 00:14:07.014 position:10% line:89% align:start
You're really pissing me off.

00:14:07.147 --> 00:14:09.517 position:30% line:83% align:start
They're always
right at each other's throats.

00:14:10.250 --> 00:14:12.119 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
They're a total liability!

00:14:12.587 --> 00:14:14.488 position:33% line:83% align:start
So commences
the first strategy meeting

00:14:14.622 --> 00:14:16.990 position:27% line:83% align:start
for the upcoming
May Inter-Academy Battle.

00:14:17.124 --> 00:14:18.693 position:7% line:89% align:start
Thank you all for coming today.

00:14:18.827 --> 00:14:22.196 position:10% line:83% align:start
Now, perhaps we should begin
with last week's promo video.

00:14:22.329 --> 00:14:24.599 position:33% line:83% align:start
Sounds good.
I can get on board with that.

00:14:24.733 --> 00:14:26.601 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yeah, let's give it a look-see.

00:14:26.735 --> 00:14:27.836 position:21% line:89% align:start
[electronic whirring]

00:14:27.968 --> 00:14:33.207 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:14:40.147 --> 00:14:42.282 position:44% line:83% align:start
Well,
that sucked even for a teaser.

00:14:42.416 --> 00:14:43.917 position:27% line:83% align:start
But it's clearly
a domination game

00:14:44.051 --> 00:14:45.953 position:27% line:83% align:start
with an emphasis
on area conquest.

00:14:46.086 --> 00:14:47.020 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:14:47.154 --> 00:14:48.889 position:10% line:89% align:start
I agree with your conclusion.

00:14:49.423 --> 00:14:51.860 position:7% line:83% align:start
Though your language could use
some work, Transfer.

00:14:51.992 --> 00:14:53.227 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
I have a lot of respect for you,

00:14:53.360 --> 00:14:54.829 position:19% line:89% align:start
so let's keep it civil.

00:14:54.962 --> 00:14:56.397 position:33% line:89% align:start
Say, Himeji.

00:14:56.531 --> 00:14:58.633 position:16% line:83% align:start
They've already released
the basic rules, haven't they?

00:14:58.767 --> 00:15:00.300 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:15:00.434 --> 00:15:02.604 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's a large-scale game adhering
to operational regulations,

00:15:02.737 --> 00:15:05.439 position:33% line:83% align:start
and it allows
for up to 100 players.

00:15:05.973 --> 00:15:09.042 position:35% line:83% align:start
"Area Steal
To Reconquer All Lost."

00:15:09.176 --> 00:15:11.679 position:7% line:83% align:start
Going by the initialism ASTRAL,
for short.

00:15:12.279 --> 00:15:13.882 position:24% line:83% align:start
The game will last
from Monday, May 9th

00:15:14.014 --> 00:15:15.482 position:19% line:89% align:start
until Friday, May 13th.

00:15:15.884 --> 00:15:18.586 position:19% line:83% align:start
Each day has one period
from 9:00 until noon,

00:15:18.720 --> 00:15:21.054 position:24% line:83% align:start
and a second period
from 2:00 until 5:00.

00:15:21.188 --> 00:15:22.791 position:35% line:83% align:start
That's ten,
split over five days.

00:15:22.923 --> 00:15:25.459 position:7% line:83% align:start
The competition will take place
in District Zero,

00:15:25.593 --> 00:15:26.994 position:19% line:83% align:start
the Special Development
District,

00:15:27.127 --> 00:15:28.429 position:10% line:89% align:start
at the center of the island.

00:15:28.830 --> 00:15:31.900 position:7% line:83% align:start
Our game field will be divided
into one million spaces.

00:15:32.032 --> 00:15:34.903 position:13% line:83% align:start
Key points known as "Bases"
will be scattered randomly.

00:15:35.302 --> 00:15:37.639 position:27% line:83% align:start
These bases will,
of course, be capturable.

00:15:38.338 --> 00:15:39.741 position:16% line:89% align:start
Two captures make a line.

00:15:39.874 --> 00:15:40.909 position:21% line:89% align:start
Three make a polygon.

00:15:41.408 --> 00:15:43.343 position:30% line:83% align:start
All the spaces
within these connected points

00:15:43.477 --> 00:15:45.412 position:33% line:83% align:start
become a part
of the owner's team's area,

00:15:45.547 --> 00:15:47.882 position:30% line:83% align:start
and will change
to the associated color.

00:15:48.015 --> 00:15:49.349 position:35% line:89% align:start
Every hour,

00:15:49.483 --> 00:15:50.885 position:19% line:83% align:start
the bases will release
special usable skills,

00:15:51.018 --> 00:15:53.153 position:24% line:83% align:start
hereafter referred
to as "spells."

00:15:53.555 --> 00:15:56.724 position:5% line:83% align:start
The game also uses what is known
as a "Freeze Time" system.

00:15:56.858 --> 00:15:59.193 position:21% line:83% align:start
Meaning, essentially,
that after you use a spell,

00:15:59.326 --> 00:16:00.895 position:24% line:83% align:start
you cannot perform
another action

00:16:01.028 --> 00:16:02.095 position:21% line:89% align:start
for a short duration.

00:16:02.229 --> 00:16:03.464 position:16% line:89% align:start
The length of Freeze Time

00:16:03.598 --> 00:16:05.065 position:33% line:83% align:start
is calculated
from the movement value

00:16:05.199 --> 00:16:07.234 position:19% line:83% align:start
specifically attributed
to each player.

00:16:07.367 --> 00:16:09.904 position:7% line:83% align:start
There are five player positions
you can assume in ASTRAL,

00:16:10.037 --> 00:16:13.140 position:19% line:83% align:start
but no overlap of roles
is permitted within a team.

00:16:13.273 --> 00:16:15.342 position:5% line:83% align:start
To win, you must either dominate
all the areas

00:16:15.476 --> 00:16:17.344 position:7% line:89% align:start
or destroy all the other teams.

00:16:17.879 --> 00:16:20.748 position:24% line:83% align:start
However, if neither
of these conditions is met,

00:16:20.882 --> 00:16:23.718 position:16% line:83% align:start
victory goes to the team
with the largest occupied area

00:16:23.852 --> 00:16:25.085 position:19% line:89% align:start
when the time runs out.

00:16:25.219 --> 00:16:27.187 position:30% line:83% align:start
Now, moving on
to the loss conditions.

00:16:27.589 --> 00:16:29.356 position:21% line:83% align:start
Each player possesses
life points,

00:16:29.490 --> 00:16:32.459 position:10% line:83% align:start
and if all of those are lost,
the player is eliminated.

00:16:32.594 --> 00:16:35.462 position:13% line:83% align:start
Players can have a maximum
of five life points.

00:16:35.597 --> 00:16:37.665 position:35% line:83% align:start
These reset
at the end of each period.

00:16:38.265 --> 00:16:40.133 position:24% line:83% align:start
If all team members
are eliminated,

00:16:40.267 --> 00:16:42.570 position:24% line:83% align:start
or if a team loses
all of their spaces,

00:16:42.704 --> 00:16:44.371 position:16% line:89% align:start
that team is eliminated.

00:16:44.806 --> 00:16:46.306 position:5% line:89% align:start
During the Inter-Academy Battle,

00:16:46.440 --> 00:16:50.110 position:13% line:83% align:start
another game entitled MTCG
will be held simultaneously.

00:16:50.612 --> 00:16:52.246 position:7% line:89% align:start
The top prize is a "Wild Card",

00:16:52.379 --> 00:16:54.916 position:33% line:83% align:start
which serves
as an invitation to ASTRAL.

00:16:55.048 --> 00:16:56.350 position:13% line:89% align:start
The player who secures this

00:16:56.483 --> 00:16:58.118 position:30% line:83% align:start
is able to join
any team of their choosing

00:16:58.252 --> 00:16:59.621 position:24% line:89% align:start
as a sixth member,

00:16:59.754 --> 00:17:02.155 position:19% line:83% align:start
allowing for an element
of unpredictability.

00:17:02.289 --> 00:17:04.726 position:7% line:83% align:start
The three most valuable pieces
of information

00:17:04.859 --> 00:17:06.260 position:16% line:89% align:start
we should be focusing on

00:17:06.393 --> 00:17:09.664 position:10% line:83% align:start
are areas, player positions,
and movement values.

00:17:09.797 --> 00:17:10.798 position:33% line:89% align:start
Interesting.

00:17:10.932 --> 00:17:12.534 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hey, Shirayuki,

00:17:12.667 --> 00:17:14.434 position:7% line:83% align:start
is there any way for us to see
what the movement values are?

00:17:14.569 --> 00:17:16.169 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] If you open
the purpose-made app

00:17:16.303 --> 00:17:17.437 position:16% line:89% align:start
released a few days ago,

00:17:17.572 --> 00:17:19.273 position:24% line:83% align:start
it should be listed
on your profile.

00:17:19.406 --> 00:17:20.808 position:10% line:89% align:start
There are 25 levels overall,

00:17:20.942 --> 00:17:23.076 position:10% line:83% align:start
and the smaller your number,
the better.

00:17:23.210 --> 00:17:24.311 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Movement values

00:17:24.444 --> 00:17:26.014 position:38% line:83% align:start
are like
a player's general rating.

00:17:26.146 --> 00:17:29.149 position:7% line:83% align:start
They're calculated using stuff
like game and trial records.

00:17:29.283 --> 00:17:30.885 position:5% line:89% align:start
Of course, for me, that means...

00:17:31.019 --> 00:17:32.754 position:38% line:83% align:start
[NANASE]
Three? That's crazy!

00:17:32.887 --> 00:17:34.689 position:10% line:83% align:start
Talk about a top-tier rating,
Shino!

00:17:34.822 --> 00:17:37.057 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Good job, Seven Star!
-Yeah, thank you.

00:17:37.190 --> 00:17:38.760 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Hang on, "Shino"?
-[NANASE] Hm.

00:17:38.893 --> 00:17:41.194 position:7% line:83% align:start
Just a little nickname for you.
No good?

00:17:41.328 --> 00:17:42.630 position:27% line:83% align:start
After the things
I've been called,

00:17:42.764 --> 00:17:43.898 position:24% line:89% align:start
that's pretty tame.

00:17:44.032 --> 00:17:44.933 position:27% line:89% align:start
Then "yes" good.

00:17:45.733 --> 00:17:47.802 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Naturally,
my movement value is a lie.

00:17:47.936 --> 00:17:50.872 position:13% line:83% align:start
My real number's not three,
it's nineteen.

00:17:51.005 --> 00:17:52.306 position:16% line:89% align:start
Kagaya bugged the screen

00:17:52.439 --> 00:17:53.942 position:21% line:83% align:start
to display something
a little more fitting.

00:17:54.074 --> 00:17:57.477 position:13% line:83% align:start
Now, I'd like us to decide
on a general plan of action.

00:17:57.845 --> 00:18:00.648 position:16% line:83% align:start
There are two key avenues
of strategy in ASTRAL.

00:18:00.782 --> 00:18:03.051 position:30% line:83% align:start
You either win
by expanding your area

00:18:03.183 --> 00:18:04.919 position:35% line:83% align:start
or you make
the other teams lose.

00:18:05.053 --> 00:18:06.788 position:21% line:83% align:start
However, since spells
are required to fight,

00:18:06.921 --> 00:18:08.823 position:24% line:83% align:start
you have to expand
your region of control,

00:18:08.957 --> 00:18:10.592 position:35% line:89% align:start
regardless.

00:18:10.725 --> 00:18:13.360 position:7% line:83% align:start
Plainly stated, both objectives
are inextricably intertwined.

00:18:13.895 --> 00:18:15.362 position:5% line:89% align:start
That leads us to the next topic.

00:18:15.730 --> 00:18:19.099 position:16% line:83% align:start
Team makeup, and deciding
who takes what position.

00:18:19.767 --> 00:18:21.636 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Here's the role breakdowns.

00:18:22.804 --> 00:18:24.572 position:16% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Getting assigned
the right position here

00:18:24.706 --> 00:18:26.007 position:30% line:89% align:start
is everything.

00:18:26.139 --> 00:18:28.076 position:21% line:83% align:start
The wrong designation
could expose me in a heartbeat.

00:18:28.208 --> 00:18:30.078 position:35% line:83% align:start
Basically,
if I don't get commander,

00:18:30.210 --> 00:18:31.012 position:30% line:89% align:start
it's all over.

00:18:31.144 --> 00:18:32.279 position:24% line:89% align:start
For everyone else,

00:18:32.412 --> 00:18:33.681 position:33% line:83% align:start
that massive
movement restriction

00:18:33.815 --> 00:18:34.882 position:24% line:89% align:start
could be crippling.

00:18:35.016 --> 00:18:36.350 position:19% line:89% align:start
But for me, it's a role

00:18:36.483 --> 00:18:38.251 position:16% line:83% align:start
that conveniently renders
my base rank redundant

00:18:38.385 --> 00:18:39.821 position:10% line:89% align:start
for the purpose of mobility.

00:18:39.954 --> 00:18:41.288 position:13% line:89% align:start
Helping me avoid suspicion.

00:18:41.421 --> 00:18:43.323 position:35% line:83% align:start
I can hide
my own low movement value

00:18:43.457 --> 00:18:45.093 position:19% line:83% align:start
behind the commander's
worse one.

00:18:45.459 --> 00:18:47.962 position:30% line:83% align:start
Any other role
would be catastrophic for me.

00:18:48.096 --> 00:18:51.164 position:10% line:83% align:start
It'd be obvious that my stats
aren't what I say they are.

00:18:51.966 --> 00:18:53.266 position:10% line:89% align:start
Plus if I get the commander,

00:18:53.400 --> 00:18:55.435 position:10% line:83% align:start
I can use its info abilities
as a smoke screen

00:18:55.570 --> 00:18:57.204 position:10% line:89% align:start
for Company-fed information.

00:18:57.337 --> 00:18:59.406 position:30% line:83% align:start
That'd give me
a considerable advantage.

00:18:59.941 --> 00:19:03.711 position:19% line:83% align:start
Let's see, I'm thinking
soldier's probably my best fit.

00:19:04.144 --> 00:19:06.714 position:7% line:83% align:start
I've got great natural reflexes
and visual acuity,

00:19:06.848 --> 00:19:08.783 position:38% line:83% align:start
so acting
as our offensive vanguard

00:19:08.916 --> 00:19:09.884 position:33% line:89% align:start
works for me.

00:19:10.018 --> 00:19:11.786 position:10% line:89% align:start
Then I think I'll be the spy.

00:19:11.919 --> 00:19:13.320 position:13% line:89% align:start
That one's perfect for me.

00:19:13.453 --> 00:19:15.657 position:30% line:83% align:start
Sneaking around
and secretly setting up traps

00:19:15.790 --> 00:19:16.758 position:27% line:89% align:start
is my specialty.

00:19:16.891 --> 00:19:18.826 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
All right, it's looking good.

00:19:18.960 --> 00:19:20.427 position:13% line:89% align:start
We're almost in the clear.

00:19:20.561 --> 00:19:22.396 position:44% line:83% align:start
Next,
I'll nab the commander position,

00:19:22.530 --> 00:19:24.565 position:30% line:83% align:start
and then Himeji
can take the guardian one.

00:19:25.265 --> 00:19:26.567 position:30% line:89% align:start
So I'll take--

00:19:26.701 --> 00:19:27.735 position:21% line:83% align:start
-[SHINJI] Commander.
-[HIROTO, SHIRAYUKI] Huh?

00:19:28.402 --> 00:19:29.904 position:13% line:89% align:start
I wish to be the commander.

00:19:30.538 --> 00:19:32.840 position:19% line:83% align:start
You want it too, right,
Shinohara?

00:19:33.775 --> 00:19:36.944 position:44% line:83% align:start
I do.
But just why are you after it?

00:19:37.078 --> 00:19:38.211 position:30% line:89% align:start
That's obvious.

00:19:38.345 --> 00:19:40.114 position:35% line:83% align:start
If we lack
a competent commander,

00:19:40.247 --> 00:19:42.449 position:27% line:83% align:start
victory in ASTRAL
is an impossibility.

00:19:42.583 --> 00:19:45.352 position:16% line:83% align:start
If that's your reasoning,
then I'm the clear choice here.

00:19:45.485 --> 00:19:46.954 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SHINJI]
No, you aren't.

00:19:47.088 --> 00:19:50.124 position:21% line:83% align:start
See, the commander's
movement value is fixed at 25.

00:19:50.257 --> 00:19:51.626 position:19% line:83% align:start
You have a lower value
than I do,

00:19:51.759 --> 00:19:53.193 position:30% line:83% align:start
so you would be
more disadvantaged

00:19:53.326 --> 00:19:54.762 position:27% line:89% align:start
by the handicap.

00:19:54.896 --> 00:19:57.364 position:10% line:83% align:start
Also, duties of the commander
involve intel gathering,

00:19:57.497 --> 00:19:59.366 position:13% line:89% align:start
analysis, and coordination.

00:19:59.499 --> 00:20:01.069 position:16% line:83% align:start
These are all specialties
of mine.

00:20:01.201 --> 00:20:02.970 position:27% line:83% align:start
Do you get that,
transfer student?

00:20:03.370 --> 00:20:06.140 position:13% line:83% align:start
The only clear choice here
is me. Not you.

00:20:06.273 --> 00:20:07.909 position:7% line:89% align:start
Stop being so stubborn, Shinji.

00:20:08.042 --> 00:20:10.945 position:21% line:83% align:start
Shino can use insane
Unique Star abilities you can't.

00:20:11.079 --> 00:20:13.181 position:7% line:83% align:start
He's the highest-ranked player
on the island.

00:20:13.313 --> 00:20:14.849 position:33% line:89% align:start
And honestly,

00:20:14.982 --> 00:20:16.584 position:7% line:83% align:start
I really don't want to be stuck
taking orders from you.

00:20:16.718 --> 00:20:18.485 position:21% line:83% align:start
Personal preferences
have nothing to do with it,

00:20:18.619 --> 00:20:20.955 position:33% line:83% align:start
this is just
about what's most appropriate.

00:20:21.589 --> 00:20:22.857 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Think!

00:20:22.990 --> 00:20:25.258 position:5% line:83% align:start
You have to deceive your enemies
and your allies.

00:20:25.392 --> 00:20:26.761 position:27% line:83% align:start
You have to make
every last one of them

00:20:26.894 --> 00:20:29.063 position:16% line:83% align:start
believe in the reputation
you've created.

00:20:29.197 --> 00:20:30.397 position:33% line:89% align:start
If you don't,

00:20:30.531 --> 00:20:31.733 position:21% line:83% align:start
this team falls apart
at the seams,

00:20:31.866 --> 00:20:33.868 position:27% line:83% align:start
and all your lies
will be laid bare.

00:20:35.036 --> 00:20:36.403 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Yo, Enomoto.

00:20:36.537 --> 00:20:38.238 position:24% line:83% align:start
Quite a forward way
of addressing your senior,

00:20:38.371 --> 00:20:39.372 position:30% line:89% align:start
but what is it?

00:20:39.907 --> 00:20:41.676 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Commander
can trade places with someone

00:20:41.809 --> 00:20:42.510 position:30% line:89% align:start
once per game.

00:20:42.944 --> 00:20:44.746 position:16% line:83% align:start
So, how about you let me
take it first?

00:20:45.345 --> 00:20:47.749 position:10% line:83% align:start
And, if my performance fails
to meet your standards,

00:20:47.882 --> 00:20:50.585 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'll surrender the position
to you without complaint.

00:20:51.652 --> 00:20:52.887 position:38% line:89% align:start
Curious.

00:20:53.020 --> 00:20:55.056 position:13% line:83% align:start
I could counter by offering
the same deal in reverse,

00:20:55.189 --> 00:20:57.125 position:27% line:89% align:start
but I'll accept,

00:20:57.257 --> 00:20:58.458 position:27% line:89% align:start
on the condition

00:20:58.593 --> 00:20:59.560 position:27% line:83% align:start
that you take out
three enemy commanders

00:20:59.694 --> 00:21:01.229 position:10% line:89% align:start
by the end of the third day.

00:21:01.361 --> 00:21:02.630 position:24% line:89% align:start
Fail in that task,

00:21:02.764 --> 00:21:04.832 position:21% line:83% align:start
and you'll hand over
the position to me.

00:21:04.966 --> 00:21:06.366 position:21% line:89% align:start
Wait, Mister Enomoto.

00:21:06.500 --> 00:21:09.003 position:7% line:83% align:start
Don't you think that condition
would be somewhat exploitable?

00:21:09.570 --> 00:21:11.506 position:16% line:83% align:start
You could easily sabotage
his progress

00:21:11.639 --> 00:21:13.641 position:27% line:83% align:start
just by refusing
to cooperate with him.

00:21:13.775 --> 00:21:16.110 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's Shirayuki Himeji, right?

00:21:16.244 --> 00:21:17.645 position:7% line:89% align:start
Your foresight is commendable,

00:21:17.779 --> 00:21:19.514 position:24% line:83% align:start
but it appears that
you're forgetting something.

00:21:19.647 --> 00:21:21.949 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Uh, forgetting something?

00:21:22.382 --> 00:21:23.718 position:35% line:89% align:start
My motive.

00:21:23.851 --> 00:21:25.452 position:24% line:83% align:start
As Eimei Academy's
student council president,

00:21:25.586 --> 00:21:27.655 position:13% line:83% align:start
my only real ambition here
is to win.

00:21:27.789 --> 00:21:30.357 position:44% line:83% align:start
See,
in the annual academy rankings,

00:21:30.490 --> 00:21:32.927 position:24% line:83% align:start
Eimei's been stuck
in fifth place for years.

00:21:33.060 --> 00:21:35.395 position:30% line:83% align:start
I'd like to see
our status elevated.

00:21:35.897 --> 00:21:37.632 position:7% line:89% align:start
With Seven Star Shinohara here,

00:21:37.765 --> 00:21:39.834 position:21% line:83% align:start
we have a good chance
of doing that this year.

00:21:39.967 --> 00:21:42.069 position:38% line:83% align:start
As such,
I would do absolutely nothing

00:21:42.203 --> 00:21:43.237 position:30% line:89% align:start
to hinder him.

00:21:43.370 --> 00:21:44.972 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Okay. Good enough for me.

00:21:45.106 --> 00:21:47.374 position:27% line:83% align:start
You have my word,
if I can't pull this off,

00:21:47.508 --> 00:21:49.143 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'll give the commander's role
to you.

00:21:50.244 --> 00:21:53.313 position:19% line:83% align:start
And I'll talk properly
for the rest of my life.

00:21:54.282 --> 00:21:55.482 position:30% line:89% align:start
[phone ringing]

00:21:56.017 --> 00:21:57.084 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[HIROTO] Hello?
-[SARASA] <i>Uh...</i>

00:21:57.218 --> 00:21:58.485 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>Shinohara? Oh, good.</i>

00:21:58.619 --> 00:22:00.021 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>If you hadn't answered,</i>
 <i>I don't know</i>

00:22:00.154 --> 00:22:01.155 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>-what I would've done.</i>
-[HIROTO] What's up?

00:22:01.289 --> 00:22:02.223 position:16% line:89% align:start
You sound kind of upset.

00:22:02.355 --> 00:22:03.356 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
 <i>Of course I am!</i>

00:22:03.490 --> 00:22:05.159 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>We're in serious trouble!</i>

00:22:05.293 --> 00:22:07.228 position:27% line:89% align:start
Trouble? How so?

00:22:07.360 --> 00:22:08.763 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
 <i>It's Sarasa!</i>

00:22:08.896 --> 00:22:10.598 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>And I'm not talking about me</i>
 <i>or the original.</i>

00:22:10.731 --> 00:22:13.701 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>A third Sarasa Saionji's</i>
 <i>just revealed herself!</i>

00:22:13.835 --> 00:22:15.603 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh... Ah?

